OL,3,CHundreds of modern slavery victims
OL,4,Cwork in UK's bars and hotels, charity
OL,5,Cwarns
OL,7,FUnseen said some workers are in debt
OL,8,Fto people in their home country but
OL,9,Fothers are "in a situation of debt
OL,10,Fbondage to their employer, paying off
OL,11,Fmoney owed incrementally through
OL,12,Fsalary deductions".
OL,14,FPeople can end up in situations where
OL,15,Fthey are left with little money to
OL,16,Flook after themselves, the charity
OL,17,Fsaid, and are unable to get out of a
OL,18,Fsituation where some employers
OL,19,Fpressure them to work long hours
OL,20,Fwithout breaks or time off in order
OL,21,Ffor them to pay off the debt.
